<DOC><DOCNO> AP891215-0106 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-15-89 1235EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a PM-WeatherpageWeather 1stLd-Writethru a0495 12-15 0808</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0495,0825</SECOND><HEAD>Dangerous Wind Chills Slap Central U.S.</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: SUBS grafs 5-13 bgng `Even more...' with 14 grafs to UPDATEwith snow conditions today in Wyoming, Colorado, Michigan, Wisconsin andelsewhere. Picks up 14th graf, `A winter....'</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Wicked northwest winds whipped snow and arctic air into thenorth-central states today, spawning subzero temperatures acrossmost of the northern Plains and Upper Mississippi Valley and windchill indexes of 50 degrees below zero.   Frigid temperatures were expected to continue this weekend asmassive arctic high pressure settled into the northern and centralPlains.   At 11 p.m. Thursday, North Dakota wind chill indexes included 55below in Fargo, 49 below in Jamestown and 43 below in Grand Forks.   Wind chill factors are the combined effect of winds and chillingtemperatures on exposed skin. Advisories for dangerous wind chillsas cold as 60 below have been posted for much of Nebraska, Kansasand Iowa today.   In north-central Wyoming, it was snowing so hard in the Big HornMountains that the Antelope Butte ski resort couldn't opened thisweekend as planned. Roads to the resort were blocked, preventing anengineer from reaching the area for an annual inspection requiredby the U.S. Forest Service, its owners said. Some 30 inches of snowhas fallen in the area.   A winter storm warning was in effect for much of northern,central and southeastern Wyoming today.   A snow and blowing snow advisory was issued for the north andcentral mountains in Colorado today after 18 inches of snow fellnear Vail Pass.   Even more snow was expected in the already blanketed Great Lakesregion. A heavy snow warning was in effect for Lake Superior'sshoreline today.   Six inches of new snow fell overnight in Wisconsin's DoorCounty, bringing the amount of accumulation since Wednesday to 30inches.   Heavy snow warnings were posted today for Michigan's western andcentral Upper Peninsula, with up to 12 inches expected in isolatedareas. The 3 below recorded in Flint this morning broke a26-year-old record low of minus 1.   Advisories for snow and blowing snow have also been issued forcentral Montana.   Snow in the middle Mississippi Valley was expected to spreadinto the Ohio Valley. In Missouri, the heaviest snow _ about 6inches _ hit the St. Louis area, but Kansas City and Kirksvillewere the coldest spots in the state with readings of 15 below and14 below respectively.   Lake snow advisories were issued for parts of western New Yorkstate.   A winter storm warning was in effect today for northernKentucky, the southern half of Indiana and southwest Ohio. A snowadvisory was issued for southeast Ohio and a winter storm watch wasposted for the northeastern part of the state.   A winter storm warning was in effect today and tonight in WestVirginia's northern mountains.   Peoria, Ill. broke an 88-year-old record for the date's coldesttemperature with 7 degrees. Other cities with record lows for thedate included Bismarck, N.D., 26; Buffalo, N.Y., 2; Rochester,N.Y., 3; Rockford, Ill., 4, and Pensacola, Fla., 27.   Temperatures Thursday warmed into the 70s across parts ofCalifornia and in extreme southern Texas.   The nation's high was 79 at Spring Valley, Calif., and San JuanCapistrano, Calif.   Other reports at 4 a.m. EST today:   _EAST: Albany, N.Y. 3 partly cloudy; Atlanta 37 partly cloudy;Boston 16 fair; Buffalo 16; Charleston, S.C. 33 fair; Chattanooga34 cloudy; Cincinnati 17 snow; Cleveland 6 cloudy; Detroit 1 fair;Hatteras 31 fair; Jacksonville 35 fair; Key West 64 partly cloudy;Knoxville 30 cloudy; Macon 29 fair; Miami 57 partly cloudy; NewYork 26 fair; Philadelphia 19 fair; Pittsburgh 8 partly cloudy;Portland, Maine 0 fair; Richmond 23 foggy; Tampa 44 partly cloudy;Washington, D.C. 24 foggy.   _CENTRAL: Birmingham 46 cloudy; Bismarck 20 fair; Chicago 2cloudy; Denver 14 snow; Des Moines 11 fair; Fort Worth 32;Indianapolis 10 snow; Kansas City 11 fair; Little Rock 39 partlycloudy; Louisville 23 snow; Memphis 46 fair; Nashville 41 cloudy;New Orleans 52 partly cloudy; North Platte 18 fair; Oklahoma City20 windy; Omaha 12 windy; Rapid City 21 fair; St. Louis 6 snow;Minneapolis-St. Paul 1 snow; Sault Ste. Marie 2 fair; San Antonio36 fair.   _WEST: Albuquerque 35 fair; Anchorage 28 cloudy; Boise 24 fair;Casper 15 snow; Fairbanks 17 fair; Great Falls 34 cloudy; Honolulu66 fair; Las Vegas 40 fair; Los Angeles 53 cloudy; Medford 27foggy; Pendleton 25 foggy; Phoenix 45 fair; Portland, Ore. 37drizzle; Reno 23 fair; Salt Lake City 32 partly cloudy; San Diego54 cloudy; San Francisco 45 hazy; Seattle 32 foggy; Spokane 29cloudy.   _INTERNATIONAL: Calgary 34 fair; Montreal 7 partly cloudy;Ottawa 0 cloudy; Regina 23 fair; Toronto 7 snow; Winnipeg 8 snow;Mexico City 46; Kingston 75 fair; Nassau 64 partly cloudy.</TEXT></DOC>